                <head>No. 41.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hall</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-04-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 21, 1886</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 341.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 480, of the 19th ultimo,
                    concerning the convention signed at Amapala, January 13, 1886, re-establishing
                    amicable relations between Nicaragua and Salvador, and have to say that the same
                    has been read with friendly interest in what touches the assured peace of the
                    sister Republics of Central America.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
